<br>
Battlefield is not a reservation system.<br>
<br>
Two guilds want to kill uber_mob_007. They are in competition with each other. The least unfair (read that carefully *least unfair* ) is to go by honourable FCFS (i.e. no training the raid, no blatant leapfrogging).<br>
<br>
If you want to set up a reservation system then go ahead, no ones stopping you. I doubt you'll manage it; there are too many complications and a player run reservation system would be too open to abuse, plus its a lot of maintanence.<br>
<br>
But without a formal structure, raids aren't going to wait around to see if anyone else was planning to kill something. Raids usually move too fast for that.<br>
<br>
Battlefield - you can post your intent and hope that anyone intending to raid that target reads it, but to my mind the Battlefield forum is primarily for letting people know about open / semi open raids so that they can attend. <br>
<br>
Remember that the people who don't read the Battlefield usually also don't post in the Battlefield; it's quite possible that they were planning their raid as long as or even longer than you.<br>
<br>
